## Introduction
This Streamlit app focuses on sentiment analysis of Twitter data. It uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques to preprocess and analyze tweets, categorizing them as positive, negative, or neutral. The app visualizes the results using word clouds, hashtag frequencies, and a pie chart for sentiment distribution.

## Analysis Section
The script begins by importing necessary libraries, loading Twitter data, and performing data preprocessing. It includes text cleaning, stemming, and the extraction of hashtags. The script generates word clouds for positive and negative sentiments, as well as bar plots displaying the most common hashtags for each sentiment.

## Streamlit App Section
The Streamlit app provides an interactive interface for users to explore sentiment analysis results. Users can view word clouds, hashtag frequencies, and sentiment distribution. The app allows users to input their own tweets for sentiment analysis and see the results in real-time.

## Conclusion
This Streamlit app offers a user-friendly way to perform Twitter Sentiment Analysis and gain insights from tweet data. It can be useful for tracking sentiment trends and understanding public opinion on various topics.

